The paper focuses on facial attribute classification using deep learning methods, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed method involves multi-task learning and multi-label classification, which are also relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of dynamic weighting and adaptive thresholding, which are techniques commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
